rahunas (0.3.0-1) experimental; urgency=low

  * Imported Upstream version 0.3.0
  * Switch to debhelper 9
    * debian/compat, debian/source/format:
      - Set compatibility to 9
      - Switch to source format 3.0 (quilt)
    * debian/control:
      - Set debhelper (>= 9~) and dh-autoreconf to Build-Deps.
      - Set libgnet-dev (>= 2.0.8~) for backports friendly.
      - Drop autoconf, automake and autotools-dev from Build-Deps as unneeded.
    * debian/rules:
      - Cleanup the rules by using the debhelper minimalist rules.
  * Update watch file for new upstream release location
  * Update files installation
    * debian/rahunas.install:
      - Install /usr/sbin/rahunas-ipacct.
    * debian/rahunas.docs:
      - Drop TODO, upstream dropped.
    * debian/rahunas-weblogin.install:
      - Install .htaccess
      - Install rahunas-db.sql to /usr/share/rahunasd.
      - Install third-party libs to /usr/share/rahunas/libs.
      - Install browscap cache files to /var/lib/rahunas/weblogin.
    * debian/rahunas-weblogin.dirs:
      - Create empty dir /var/lib/rahunas/weblogin/data/template/{cache,compile}
    * debian/rahunas-weblogin.links:
      - Create symlinks /var/lib/rahunas/weblogin/data to
        /usr/share/rahunas/data.
    * debian/rahunas-weblogin.postinst:
      - Change owner of /var/lib/rahunas/weblogin/data to www-data.
  * Add new package "rahunas-netsnmp-module"
    * debian/control:
      - Add rahunas-netsnmp-module package.
      - Add libsnmp-dev to Build-deps as it required by netsnmp-module build.
    * debian/rahunas.postinst:
      - Add group "rahunas"
      - Set permission to writable by group rahunas as it require by
        netsnmp-module to work properly.
    * debian/rahunas.postrm:
      - Remove group "rahunas" on purge.
    * debian/rules:
      - Add enable-netsnmp-module to build configuration.
    * debian/RAHUNAS-MIB:
      - The MIB file of RahuNAS, added to install with the package
    * debian/patches/fix-netsnmp-module-db-path.patch:
      - Add patch to fix the db path which has been moved to /var/lib/rahunas/db
  * Add $remote_fs to Required-{Start,Stop} init script
  * Update copyright file
    * debian/copyright:
      - Switch to copyright format version 1.0.
      - Update copyright years.
      - Add copyright for source files.
  * Update watch file, add cryptographic upstream tarball signature verification
    * debian/watch:
      - Update upstream tarball release location.
    * debian/upstream/signing-key.asc:
      - Add cryptographic upstream tarball signature verification.

